AGI - Manifestations throughout Iran to support the "liberation" of Palestine and to give the commiate to the seven "pasdarans" left killed in an attack on the Iranian consulate in Damascus, an attack that Tehran attributes to Israel. The Iranian broadcaster Press TV, 'voice' of the regime that broadcasts in English, reports that millions of people are gathering. According to the official press agency Irna, marches began around 10:00 local time in various parts of the country (from the north-eastern province of Khorasan Razavi to the most south, Sistan and Baluchistan) and will be held in 2 thousand points of the Persian nation.
&nbsp;
The protesters celebrate the 'Day of al Quds', the Day of Jerusalem, established in 1979 by the ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini to demand the liberation of Palestine and the fall of Israel, and commemorates the last Friday of Ramadan, the sacred month to Muslims. In conjunction with the 'Day of Al Quds', the funeral ceremony is held in Tehran for the seven 'Guardians of the Revolution', including two generals, who were killed on Monday in the attack on the Iranian consulate in Damascus. It was the worst blow to this elite military group since the death of Suniman Qassem, the powerful Iranian general who led the Al Quds Force of the Guardians of the Revolution until he was killed by the United States in 2020 in a bombing in Iraq.
&nbsp;
The Supreme Guide of Iran, the Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, assured that Israel will pay for the death of the military: "The wicked regime will be punished by our brave men. We will make them repent of this crime and others like, with the help of God." Faced with these threats of Iranian retaliation, Israel is in "maximum alert" and ready to react "to various scenarios".

